executeIntent(address,bytes32,bytes).details: Function to execute an intent by providing the solver's address and the payload.

params.intentId: The unique identifier of the intent to be executed.
params.payload: The payload associated with the intent, encoded in bytes.
params.solver: The address of the solver attempting to perform the intent.

placeIntent((bytes,bytes,address,address.details: Function to place an intent within the system.

params.intent: The Intent struct containing details about the intent.

returns._0: The unique identifier of the placed intent.

previewIntent(address,bytes32,bytes).details: Function to preview an intent before execution, considering the solver and payload.

params.intentId: The unique identifier of the intent to be previewed.
params.payload: The payload associated with the intent, encoded in bytes.
params.solver: The address of the solver attempting to preview the intent.

returns._0: A boolean indicating whether the intent meets the validator's criteria for execution.
